
[1]monk

   MONK, n. [L. monachus.] A man who retires from the ordinary temporal
   concerns of the world, and devotes himself to religion. Monks usually
   live in monasteries, on entering which they take a vow to observe
   certain rules. Some however live as hermits in solitude,and others have
   lived a strolling life without any fixed residence.
